The single session may actually work for a desktop app going to a dedicated back end (meaning no updates outside the current session).  With an embedded database this would work very well.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In the web app I ended up creating one session per request (if one is needed) and using structuremap to manage the cleanup.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I&#039;m far from an expert on this stuff, but it is highly dependent on the nature of the application you&#039;re working on.  I&#039;ll try to expand on this later, if for nothing else but to help clarify some of my own thoughts on the question.
